User Guide â€“ Supermarket Sales Data Entry & Dashboard
1. Overview
This guide provides instructions for using the Streamlit-based supermarket sales data entry application. The application allows users to input sales data into a MySQL database, manage multi-product invoices, and view updated insights via a connected Power BI dashboard.
2. Requirements
- Python 3.8 or later installed on your system.
- Required Python libraries installed: Streamlit, Pandas, MySQL Connector, SQLAlchemy.
- MySQL server installed and running.
- Power BI Desktop (or Power BI Service) for dashboard visualization.
- Internet browser for accessing the Streamlit web app.
3. Installation
1. Clone or download the project repository from GitHub.
2. Navigate to the project folder in your terminal.
3. Install dependencies:
   pip install -r requirements.txt
4. Ensure the MySQL database `supermarket_db` is created.
5. Update the database credentials in `app.py` to match your MySQL configuration.
4. Starting the Application
1. Open a terminal in the project folder.
2. Run the following command:
   streamlit run app.py
3. The app will open automatically in your default web browser.
5. Entering a New Invoice
1. The application will automatically generate a new Invoice ID.
2. Select the following details from dropdowns or input fields:
   - City (Branch will be automatically assigned)
   - Customer Type
   - Gender
   - Date & Time
   - Payment Method
   - Rating
3. Add product details:
   - Select Product Line
   - Enter Unit Price and Quantity
   - Click 'Add Product' to include it in the invoice.
4. Review the product list displayed on the screen.
5. Use the ðŸ—‘ button to remove any mistakenly added products.
6. The Final Invoice Total will be displayed automatically.
7. Click 'Submit Invoice' to save the data into the MySQL database.
6. Viewing Data in Power BI
1. Open your Power BI dashboard connected to the MySQL database.
2. Click 'Refresh' in Power BI to fetch the latest data.
3. View updated KPIs, product performance charts, and customer satisfaction metrics.
7. Tips & Best Practices
- Ensure MySQL is running before starting the Streamlit app.
- Always double-check product details before submission.
- Use the delete option to correct mistakes before finalizing the invoice.
